**Russia May Launch New Wave of Mobilization to Gather 800,000 Troops for Ukraine Battles**
According to military expert and former Ukrainian army colonel, Vladyslav Selezniv, Russia may start a new wave of mobilization to gather an 800,000-strong group for battles in Ukraine. Selezniv stated that the Russian army, which was professional before the full-scale invasion in 2022, now consists of 'chmobiliki' (conscripts seeking high pay for killing Ukrainians) and mercenaries recruited worldwide. He said that only a small segment of the Russian army still remembers how to fight properly, while the majority were conscripted during the partial mobilization in September 2022. Selezniv believes that Russia can still compensate for the catastrophic level of losses, with up to 30-35,000 military casualties per month. He predicts that without large-scale mobilization, it will be difficult for Russia to gather the required number of troops by the end of the year. Selezniv thinks that Putin may announce the new mobilization as early as the first weeks of September, coinciding with the Russian parliamentary elections. He also predicts that the new mobilization will be similar to the previous one, with many conscripts being sent to the front lines and dying soon after. Selezniv believes that Russia lacks both material and human resources to sustain a long-term war effort.
