**Peskov: No Discussion About Mobilization in Russia**
Russian President's press secretary, Dmitry Peskov, stated that there is no discussion about mobilization in Russia. When asked if there is a shortage of volunteers in the special operation zone and if mobilization is needed, Peskov replied, 'No one is talking about mobilization, there is no discussion about it.' This comes after partial mobilization was announced in Russia on September 21, 2022, and was later declared completed by President Vladimir Putin on October 31, 2022, with over 300,000 people being called up. In May 2024, Defense Minister Andrei Belyusov stated that the Russian army needs to be replenished, but 'there is no talk of mobilization, of extraordinary measures'.
