**Russian Military: Bring Friend, Earn Bonus**
The Russian authorities have introduced a new initiative to encourage citizens to sign contracts with the Russian Ministry of Defense (MoD) for military service. The initiative offers 100,000 rubles (about $1,150) to anyone who brings a friend to the military enlistment office, provided the friend signs a contract. Yuri Sinelshchikov, Deputy Chairperson of the Russian State Duma Committee on State Construction and Legislation, has expressed concerns about the potential abuse of this system. Additionally, the Russian army is developing a military motorcyclist specialty in response to an increase in Ukrainian drone strikes and aerial reconnaissance. The Kremlin will begin training motorcycle specialists on October 1. According to the Institute for the Study of War (ISW), a new mobilization wave will be necessary by the end of 2024 if Moscow is to achieve its military aims in Ukraine.
